title: High-energy fission of heavy elements. Nuclear charge dependence

x4codes.hlp: University of Chicago, IL, United States of America

x4freetext: High-energy fission of heavy elements. Nuclear charge
dependence
The correction factors for absorption and scattering
of nuclides decaying by beta emission of low energy
were large, from 1.2 to 1.9, and varied considerably
depending on the sample weight.
In all, it was expected that most of the reported
cross sections may be in error by as much as 30%.
Data taken from PR,99,1459,1955--Table I.
BIB CORRECTIONS.
DR "CUM" and uncertainty added in subentry
7 and Cu61 moved to subentry 27
